Samsung is rolling out an update which will bring a variety of Galaxy Watch Active features to older Samsung smartwatches including the regular Galaxy Watch, the Gear S3, and the Gear Sport, Engadget reports. Features that will be made available in the update include the Watch Activeâ€™s UI interface and new health tracking tools. The updated interface will make it easier to navigate through the features of the smartwatch, and will also provide an aesthetic improvement for older smartwatch users. It will also allow for the toggling of Goodnight Mode, and will allow users to control how often Daily Briefings occur. The update also includes improved fitness tracking, high heart-rate alerts, and the capability to track outdoor swimming. Another reported benefit is improved battery life through superior memory management and display setting adjustments.